Linde Plans to Raise 2010 Dividend by Almost 20%, FAZ Reports

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-03-05T12:46:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-05/linde-plans-to-raise-2010-dividend-by-almost-20-faz-reports.html
  Linde AG (LIN)  plans to raise its dividend
by almost 20 percent after “record earnings” in 2010,
Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung reported, without saying how it
got the information.  The company may pay a dividend of 2.15 euros ($3.01) per
share, compared with 1.80 euros per share the year before, FAZ
said, citing unidentified people. According to Bloomberg data,
Linde may raise its dividend to 2.10 euros.  Linde declined to comment on the German newspaper’s report,
FAZ said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net  